criteria.textblock:
        -  All participants will be adult women

        INCLUSION CRITERIA ARE:

          1. <TAB>being between 18 and 50 years old;

          2. <TAB>having a self reported body mass index of greater than or equal to 25;

          3. <TAB>having the ability to read, write, and converse in English;

          4. <TAB>being able to come to the NIH Clinical Center for one visit.

        EXCLUSION CRITERIA INCLUDE:

          1. <TAB>having a vestibular or seizure disorder;

          2. <TAB>having a high propensity for motion sickness;

          3. <TAB>known pregnancy;

          4. <TAB>uncorrected low vision or hearing;

          5. <TAB>inability to complete tasks in the virtual environment;

          6. <TAB>being or training to become a physician;
